The input integer `n` must be greater than or equal to 1.
The length of the 2D integer array `edges` must be greater than or equal to 0.
Each subarray `edges[i]` must have a length of 2.
The values of `a_i` and `b_i` in each subarray `edges[i]` must be between 0 and `n-1`, inclusive.
The values of `a_i` and `b_i` in each subarray `edges[i]` must be different.
There should be no repeated edges in the `edges` array.
